wikipedia_page.main: Hon. Walter Frederick Nutt OBE (1874-14 November 1940) was Managing Director of The Straits Trading Company (1918–21), at the time one of the largest tin smelting companies in the world, a member of the Federal Malay States Legislative Council and a prominent freemason who was District Grand Master of the Eastern Archipelago (1919–23).
